HEADWORD: Sheephook
<hw>Sheep"hook`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>A hook fastened to
pole, by which shepherds lay hold on the legs or necks of their sheep; a
shepherd's crook.</def> <rj><au>Dryden.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

